FORMAT: 1A
HOST: https://api.example.com

# Task API

A small API Blueprint example describing a task list.

Recognized by the format-detection sniffer via the `FORMAT: 1A` marker (routes to
the `api-blueprint` REST format). The `+ Attributes` data structures (MSON)
describe the Task resource that becomes a catalog class.

## Tasks Collection [/tasks]

### List all tasks [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array[Task])

### Create a task [POST]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (NewTask)

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Task)

## Task [/tasks/{id}]

+ Parameters
    + id (string) - Unique task identifier.

### Get a task [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (Task)

+ Response 404

# Data Structures

## Task (object)
+ id: `t-123` (string, required) - Unique task identifier.
+ title: `Buy milk` (string, required) - Short summary of the task.
+ done: false (boolean) - Whether the task is complete.
+ dueDate: `2026-01-31` (string, optional) - Due date (ISO 8601).

## NewTask (object)
+ title: `Buy milk` (string, required) - Short summary of the task.
+ dueDate: `2026-01-31` (string, optional) - Due date (ISO 8601).
